Planned Changes for Safety Improvements

Safety improvements continue as an ongoing process at the facility and are facilitated by the accidental release prevention programs. Some of the initiatives for continuing improvement include:
-- Evaluation of an alternative chemical for chlorine; 
-- Training in incident investigation methods for identified personnel;
-- Additional audits of MOC documentation by the PSM Coordinator;
-- Significant revisions to the MOC and PSSR procedures with additional training for  identified plant personnel;
-- Updating and enhancing operating procedures on a continual basis, including use of graphics where appropriate to assist in operator training/understanding; and  
-- Updating maintenance procedures and training on a continual basis.
